{"bill":{"bill_id":1648915,"change_hash":"b5fa47c5a81d6775f35387e5469615f8","session_id":1988,"session":{"session_id":1988,"state_id":46,"year_start":2023,"year_end":2023,"prefile":0,"sine_die":0,"prior":0,"special":0,"session_tag":"Regular Session","session_title":"2023 Regular Session","session_name":"2023 Regular Session"},"url":"https:\/\/legiscan.com\/VA\/bill\/HB1742\/2023","state_link":"https:\/\/lis.virginia.gov\/cgi-bin\/legp604.exe?231+sum+HB1742","completed":0,"status":1,"status_date":"2023-01-09","progress":[{"date":"2023-01-09","event":1},{"date":"2023-01-09","event":9}],"state":"VA","state_id":46,"bill_number":"HB1742","bill_type":"B","bill_type_id":"1","body":"H","body_id":7,"current_body":"H","current_body_id":7,"title":"Virginia student environmental literacy; grant fund and program.","description":"Virginia student environmental literacy; plan; grant fund Virginia student environmental literacy; plan; grant fund and program. Requires the Board of Education, in consultation with the Office of Environmental Education at the Department of Conservation and Recreation, The Science Museum of Virginia, any other stakeholder that it deems appropriate, and the public, and in order to assist each local school board in developing and implementing a program of instruction for grades kindergarten through 12 that is aligned to the Standards of Learning and emphasizes environmental literacy as an essential skill and concept of citizenship that is necessary for responsible participation in American society and in the international community, to establish and update at least once every five years a Virginia student environmental literacy plan (the plan) that includes certain descriptions and (i) prepares students to understand, analyze, and address the major environmental challenges facing the Commonwealth and the United States; (ii) provides field experiences as part of regular school curricula and creates programs that contribute to healthy lifestyles through outdoor recreation and sound nutrition; and (iii) creates opportunities for the enhanced and ongoing professional development of teachers that improves teachers' environmental subject matter knowledge and pedagogical skills in teaching about environmental issues, including the use of interdisciplinary, field-based, and research-based learning and innovative technology in the classroom. The bill establishes the Virginia Student Environmental Literacy Plan Grant Fund and Program, to be administered by the Department of Education, for the purpose of awarding grants on a competitive basis to any local school board that seeks assistance to initiate, expand, or improve teacher professional development opportunities or student environmental education programs that align with the content and objectives of the plan.","pending_committee_id":151,"committee":{"committee_id":151,"chamber":"H","chamber_id":7,"name":"Education"},"referrals":[{"date":"2023-01-09","committee_id":151,"chamber":"H","chamber_id":7,"name":"Education"},{"date":"2023-01-24","committee_id":4572,"chamber":"H","chamber_id":7,"name":"Education: Early Childhood\/Innovation"},{"date":"2023-02-07","committee_id":151,"chamber":"H","chamber_id":7,"name":"Education"}],"history":[{"date":"2023-01-09","action":"Prefiled and ordered printed; offered 01\/11\/23 23100102D","chamber":"H","chamber_id":7,"importance":0},{"date":"2023-01-09","action":"Referred to Committee on Education","chamber":"H","chamber_id":7,"importance":1},{"date":"2023-01-24","action":"Assigned Education sub: Early Childhood\/Innovation","chamber":"H","chamber_id":7,"importance":0},{"date":"2023-01-25","action":"Subcommittee recommends laying on the table (5-Y 3-N)","chamber":"H","chamber_id":7,"importance":0},{"date":"2023-02-07","action":"Left in Education","chamber":"H","chamber_id":7,"importance":0}],"sponsors":[{"people_id":1478,"person_hash":"cnprvkye","party_id":"1","state_id":46,"party":"D","role_id":1,"role":"Rep","name":"Betsy Carr","first_n